Spain’s Unemployed May Reach 5 Million, Gomez Tells Expansion

-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 
2011-04-16T07:04:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-16/spain-s-unemployed-may-reach-5-million-gomez-tells-expansion.html
The number of unemployed in  Spain 
may reach 5 million, Spanish Labor Minister Valeriano Gomez said
in an interview with  Expansion .  Spain will reach the 5 million mark if the active
population continues to grow and jobs aren’t created, Gomez told
the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in Madrid at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
